meta_review.summary:
The reviewers have pointted out four key waeknesses preventing this paper to be accepted. 

(1) Writting and organization: the description of the model architecture in the paper is disorganized, and it is unclear how each module actually works. There is a lack of complete mathematical formulation, and the architectural description is not clear enough; 
(2) Experiments: The experimental results are deemed less persuasive due to the use of outdated baselines and the absence of comparisons with recent state-of-the-art (SOTA) models; 
(3) Technical details: While TIM emphasizes interpretability via component-wise attribution, the current qualitative and quantitative evaluations of these claims are considered limited; 
(4) Limited novelty: the innovation of the work is limited, specifically regarding the "Axis-wise Linear Self-Attention," which appears to be directly adapted from Linear attention, yet there are no relevant citations. 

Given the above major, I recommend rejecting this paper.
